{"id":"2211.07537","submitter":"Bernard Derrida","authors":"Bernard Derrida","title":"Cross-overs of Bramson's shift at the transition between pulled and\n  pushed fronts","comments":null,"journal-ref":null,"doi":"10.1007/s10955-023-03077-8","report-no":null,"categories":"nlin.PS math-ph math.MP nlin.SI","license":"http://arxiv.org/licenses/nonexclusive-distrib/1.0/","abstract":"  The Bramson logarithmic shift of the position of pulled fronts is a universal\nfeature common to a large class of monostable traveling wave equations. As one\nvaries the non-linearities it so happens that one can observe, at some critical\nnon linearity, a transition from pulled fronts to pushed fronts. At this\ntransition the Bramson shift is modified. In the limit where time goes to\ninfinity and the non-linearity becomes critical, the position of the front\nexhibits a cross-over. The goal of the present note is to give the expression\nof this cross-over function, for a particular model which is exactly soluble,\nwith the hope that this expression would remain valid for more general\ntraveling wave equations at the transition between pulled and pushed fronts.\nOther cross-over functions are also obtained, for this particular model, to\ndescribe the dependence on initial conditions or the effect of a cut-off.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Thu, 3 Nov 2022 15:07:31 GMT"}],"update_date":"2023-03-22"}
